<item>
            <title>[SPR-2041] shouldn&apos;t AbstractDataBoundFormElementTag.getName() return the full path by default?</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2041</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Problem exists in current CVS.  With &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2040&quot; title=&quot;AbstractDataBoundFormElementTag looks for nested path in wrong scope.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2040&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-2040&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; open, form tags don&apos;t work correctly with nested paths anyway, but if they did they still shouldn&apos;t bind properly because getName() is implemented as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;getPath();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t the implementation be:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;getBindPath(getPath());&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="14008">SPR-2041</key>
            <summary>shouldn&apos;t AbstractDataBoundFormElementTag.getName() return the full path by default?</summary>
